Class AbstractNavigationElement

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jcvi.jillion.assembly.consed.nav.AbstractNavigationElement
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    NavigationElement
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ConsensusNavigationElement, ReadNavigationElement

    public abstract class AbstractNavigationElement
extends Object
implements NavigationElement
    AbstractNavigationElement is an abstract implementation of NavigationElement that manages all the common fields of a NavigationElement.
    Author:
    dkatzel

        public AbstractNavigationElement(NavigationElement.Type type,
                                 String targetId,
                                 Range ungappedPositionRange,
                                 String comment)
        Constructs a new NavigationElement.
        Parameters:
        type - the Type of the element; cannot be null.
        targetId - the id of the target of that is to be navigated.
        ungappedPositionRange - the ungapped position range of this element; cannot be null.
        comment - a comment that describes why this element exists (may be null).
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if type, targetId or ungappedPositionRange are null.

      • getUngappedPositionRange

        public Range getUngappedPositionRange()
        Get the ungapped position range of this element on the target coordinate system. For example, if this element is a NavigationElement.Type.CONSENSUS type, then this range refers to the consensus positions; if this element is a NavigationElement.Type.READ then this range refers to the read positions.
        Specified by:
        getUngappedPositionRange in interface NavigationElement
        Returns:
        the Range of this element (probably in CoordinateSystem#RESIDUE_BASED); never null.
